      <cell id="nesvzpmk">
        <desc><![CDATA[&lt;p&gt;Credibility lives here. Don&#039;t compete with ASPEN, complement it. Clinicians want condensed, digestible guideline summaries (full guidelines run 40–60 pages). &quot;What&#039;s New &amp; Emerging Research&quot; should update regularly and be promoted via email/LinkedIn to drive return visits.&lt;/p&gt;]]></desc>
        <order>6000</order>
        <level>1</level>
        <text>Evidence &amp;amp; Guidelines</text>
        <contents lang="en_US">
          <status>qodbev</status>
        </contents>
      </cell>
      <cell id="vhlnv2dw">
        <desc>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Highest differentiation potential. Clinicians want tools they can use in the moment, calculators, quick-reference downloads, scenario-based micro-learning, and accessible video. CE &amp;amp; Professional Development is a strong long-term hook, as CE credit is a primary reason clinicians visit competitor sites.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</desc>
        <order>7000</order>
        <level>1</level>
        <text>Tools &amp;amp; Resources</text>
        <contents lang="en_US">
          <status>6hafjfe</status>
        </contents>
      </cell>
      <cell id="ecumou1jb2prw2fd">
        <desc>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Covers the patient populations clinicians actually see. Oncology, Critical Care, and Intestinal Failure are highest priority. Home &amp;amp; Ambulatory PN is a fast-growing area with underprepared clinicians, an important differentiator. Pediatrics &amp;amp; Neonatal should be treated as its own clinical world, not a footnote.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</desc>
        <order>5000</order>
        <level>1</level>
        <text>Therapeutic Areas</text>
        <contents lang="en_US">
          <status>6hafjfe</status>
        </contents>
      </cell>
      <cell id="cknyoqnuzyiwish">
        <desc>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;The section experienced clinicians will return to repeatedly. Prescription writing, monitoring, and complications were the most-requested content areas across all stakeholder interviews. Format content for fast, practical use algorithms, protocols, quick-reference summaries. An interactive PN prescription practice tool was specifically requested and would drive repeat visits.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</desc>
        <level>1</level>
        <order>2000</order>
        <text>Clinical Practice</text>
        <contents lang="en_US">
          <status>6hafjfe</status>
        </contents>
      </cell>
      <cell id="2gayqnnzqgd">
        <desc>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Highest-priority section for launch. Research confirmed a widespread foundational knowledge gap from clinicians writing orders they don&amp;#039;t fully understand, to nurses monitoring PN patients without proper training. Serves novice-to-intermediate audiences and is a natural MSL conversation starter.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</desc>
        <level>1</level>
        <order>1000</order>
        <text>PN Fundamentals</text>
        <contents lang="en_US">
          <status>6hafjfe</status>
        </contents>
      </cell>
      <cell id="bu0xth1shp">
        <desc>&amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Critical trust-builder given the non-branded nature of the site. Clearly articulate the site&amp;#039;s educational independence and Fresenius Kabi&amp;#039;s role as a supporter, not a content controller. Contact page can double as a soft lead capture for MSL follow-up.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;</desc>
